The chairman of Abuja Municipal Area Council (AMAC) Abdullahi Adamu Candido, has said the council would soon commence the disbursement of scholarship awards to students from the council in tertiary institutions. The chairman, who was represented by his vice-chairman, Lawrence Onuchuwku, made this known after the celebration of the Nigeria 59th Independence in Orozo on Tuesday. He said the scholarship was part of efforts of the council to make the lives of residents better, urging residents of the council to make the administration with prayers. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY He said the executive would do its best to serve the public. “We have signed into law a welfare package for the past heroes of the AMAC in the spirit of the birthday of our dear country and area council by encouraging those who have served in AMAC in various capacities,” he said while he assured residents of efficient service delivery. AMAC screens students for scholarship Candido wants automatic employment for UniAbuja best graduating student Minister halts FCT tenement rates collection